pan=\"2\"|2013\u2013present || ''[[Jabardasth (comedy show)|Jabardasth]]''  || rowspan=\"7\"|''[[ETV Network]]'' || Team Leader\n|-\n|''[[Extra Jabardasth]]''|| Team Leader\n|-\n\n| 2016 || Naa Show Naa Ishtam ||  Host for 1 episode\n|-\n| 2016\u20132017 || ''[[Dhee Ultimate Dance Show|Dhee Jodi \u2013 Season 09]]''|| Team Leader & Winner\n|-\n| 2017\u20132018 || ''[[Dhee Ultimate Dance Show|Dhee \u2013 Season 10]]''|| Team Leader & Winner\n|-\n|2018\u20132019 || ''[[Dhee Ultimate Dance Show|Dhee Jodi \u2013 Season 11]]'' || Team Leader & Runner-up\n|-\n| 2017\u2013present || ''[[Pove Pora]]''|| Host\n|-\n|2018 || ''Jackpot \u2013 2'' || ''[[Sun TV Network]]''|| Host for only 4 episodes\n|-\n|2019 || Drama Juniors Blockbuster Special || ''[[Zee Telugu]]''|| Host \n|-\n|2019\u2013present|| ''[[Dhee Ultimate Dance Show|Dhee Champions \u2013 Season 12]]''||''[[ETV Network]]'' || Team Leader\n|-\n|2019 || Ali Tho Saradhaga || ''[[ETV Network]]''|| Guest \n|-\n|}\n\n== Television films ==\n\n[[ETV Network]] Festival shows are huge hit among the audience. They have excelled in bringing festivity, tradition, celebration to the show. The shows comprises members of Jabardasth, Extra Jabardasth, Dhee Ultimate Dance Show, Pataas, Pove Pora and Star Mahila along with Celebrity guests for the events, which is successful in making and telecasting of Festival celebrations till date in reference to the Culture.\n[[File:Sudigali Sudheer.png|thumbnail|right|upright=1.15|alt=|Sudigali Sudheer in [[ETV Network|ETV]] Sankranthi Special Event'''''\" Sarada Sankranthi \"''''' ]]\n\nThis is the list of Television film of this team, which is also available on YouTube.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n\n! S.No\n! Year\n! Event\n! Note\n|-\n\n|01\n|2014\n|''New Year Special 2015'' \n|\n|-\n\n|02\n| 2015\n|''New Year Special 2016'' \n|\n|-\n\n|03\n|  rowspan=\"5\" | 2016\n|''Ugadi Ullasam''\n|\n|-\n\n|04\n|''Hai Hai Vinayaka'' \n|\n|-\n\n|05 \n|''Dasara Mahotsavam''\n|\n|-\n\n|06\n|''Sambaram''\n|\n|-\n\n|07 \n|''Welcome to the Party 2017''\n|\n|-\n\n|08 \n| rowspan=\"6\" | 2017\n|''Sankranthi Pandem Kollu'' \n|\n|-\n\n|09\n|''Ugadi 369'' \n|\n|-\n\n|10\n|''Ganapati Bappa Moriya''\n| Co-Hosted with [[Pradeep Machiraju]]\n|-\n\n|11\n|''Dasara Mahotsavam'' \n|\n|-\n\n|12 \n|''Pandaga Chesko'' \n| Host\n|-\n\n|13\n|''It's Time to Party 2018'' \n| Host\n|-\n\n|14 \n| rowspan=\"6\" | 2018\n|''Saradaga Sankranti'' \n|\n|-\n\n|15 \n|''Aha Naa Pellanta'' \n|\n|-\n\n|16 \n|''Vachadayyo Swamy''\n|\n|-\n\n|17\n|''Sarrainollu''\n|\n|-\n\n|18\n|''Tarajuvvalu''\n|\n|-\n\n|19\n|''Evadi Gola Vadidi''\n| Host\n|-\n\n|20 \n| rowspan=\"8\" | 2019\n|''Sakutumba Saparivara Sametamga'' \n|Introduced his family as part of show.\n|-\n\n|21\n|''Sudheer Gadi Pelli Gola''\n| Co-Hosted with [[Pradeep Machiraju]]\n|-\n\n|22\n|''Ugadi Allulu''\n| Co-Hosted with [[Pradeep Machiraju]] in [[Zee Telugu]]\n|-\n\n|23\n|''Avunu Valliddaru Godavapaddaru''\n|\n|-\n\n|24\n|''Sudheer Gadi Intlo Deyyam''\n| Host\n|-\n\n|25\n|''Uttama Purushulu''\n|\n|-\n\n|26\n|''Zee Telugu Kutumbam Awards''\n| Co-Hosted with Anchor Ravi and Shyamala in [[Zee Telugu]]\n|-\n\n|27\n|''Aadavari Partylaki Ardhale Verule''\n|\n|-\n\n|28\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2020\n|''Amma Nanna O Sankranti''\n| \n|-\n\n|29\n|''Pandaga Sir Pandaga Anthe''\n|\n|-\n\n|}\n\n== Awards and recognition ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" align=center cellspacing=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" style=\"background:#f7f8ff; text-align=center; border: 1px solid #88a; padding: 5px; font-size: 100%; width: 88%;\"\n|+ style=\"background : #ccf\" colspan=\"3\"  | Awards\n! Year \n! Awards\n! Category\n! Nominee / Nominated Work\n! Result\n|-style=\"text-align: center;\"\n| 2018\n| [[Zee Telugu| Zee Telugu TV]] <br> Comedy Awards\n| Best Comedy Gang on Television\n| Sudigali Sudheer and Team\n|{{won}}\n|-style=\"text-align: center;\"\n| 2019\n| [[TV9 (Telugu)|TV9 Telugu]] <br> TV Awards\n| Best Male Anchor \n| Sudigali Sudheer\n|{{won}}\n|-style=\"text-align: center;\"\n| 2019\n| Padma Mohana <br> TV Awards 2019\n| Best Entertainer Award \n| Sudigali Sudheer\n|{{won}}\n|}\n\n== See also ==\n[[Annapurna Studios]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category-inline}}\n*{{Facebook|SudigaliSudheerOfficial}}\n*{{Twitter|sudheeranand}}\n*{{Instagram|sudheeranandbayana}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sudheer, Sudigali}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Indian male film actors]]\n[[Category:1987 births]]\n[[Category:Male actors in Telugu cinema]]\n[[Category:Male actors in Telugu television]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian male actors]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Vijayawada]]\n[[Category:Indian male television actors]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=March 2018}}\n{{infobox person\n| nationality        = Indian\n| name               = Sudigali Sudheer\n| image              = File:Sudigali_Sudheer.jpg\n| caption            = Sudigali Sudheer in 50th episode of ''[[Pove Pora]]'' photoshoot\n| birth_name         = '''Sudheer Anand Bayana'''\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|df=y|1987|5|19}}\n| birth_place        = [[Vijayawada]],<br /> [[Andhra Pradesh]],<br /> [[India]]\n| occupation         = {{bulleted list|Actor|Comedian|Dancer|[[Magician (illusionist)|Magician]]|Singer|Television Presenter}}\n| module             = {{Listen|embed=yes|pos=center|filename=Sudigali Sudheer Interview.flac|title=Sudigali Sudheer Voice|type=speech|description= from an Interview in March 2017<ref>{{cite web|title= Sudigali Sudheer Interview |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=F-IH-kH5Cho|work=Telugu Film Nagar|accessdate=17 March 2017}}</ref>}}\n\n| family             = ''Dev Anand Bayana'' (Father),<br />  ''Nagarani Bayana'' (Mother),<br /> ''Rohan Bayana'' (Brother),<br />  ''Ramya Bayana'' (Sister in Law), <br> ''Swetha Anand Pilla'' (Sister), <br> ''Venkat Pilla'' (Brother in Law), <br> ''Yoshita (Yoshi)'' (Niece)\n| years_active       = 2010\u2013present\n| known_for          = ''[[Extra Jabardasth]]'', ''[[Dhee Ultimate Dance Show]]'', ''[[Pove Pora]]''\n| awards             = See [[#Awards and recognition|awards]]\n}}\n\n'''Sudigali Sudheer''' (born '''Sudheer Anand ''' on 19 May 1987) is a [[Telugu language]] actor and a comedian, who is known for his performance in the [[List of Telugu-language television channels|Telugu-language television channel]] comedy shows ''[[Jabardasth (comedy show)|Jabardasth]]'' and ''[[Extra Jabardasth]]''. He is also a team leader on ''[[Dhee Ultimate Dance Show]]'' for season 9, season 10, season 11 and season 12.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/telugu/Guess-who-made-Sudigali-Sudheer-day-unforgettable/articleshow/51311466.cms|title=Sudigali Sudheer: Guess who made Sudigali Sudheer day unforgettable|work=The Times of India|access-date=8 March 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/telugu/Anchors-Rashmi-and-Sudigali-Sudheer-swaps-roles/articleshow/54763176.cms|title=Rashmi sudigali sudheer: Anchors Rashmi and Sudigali Sudheer swaps roles|work=The Times of India|access-date=9 October 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/telugu/sudigali-sudheer-is-the-new-host-of-jackpot-2/articleshow/63693210.cms|title=Jackpot 2: Sudigali Sudheer is the new host of 'Jackpot 2'|work=The Times of India|access-date=10 April 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/telugu/Sudigali-Sudheer-spotted-at-Niagara-falls/articleshow/49871303.cms|title=Sudigali Sudheer: Sudigali Sudheer spotted at Niagara falls|work=The Times of India|access-date=21 November 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tollywood.net/rashmi-gautham-and-sudigali-sudheer-impressed-from-their-first-night-room/|title=Rashmi Gautam and Sudigali Sudheer impressed from their first night room|work=tollywood.net|access-date=21 March 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/telugu/Sudigali-Sudheer-spotted-at-tower-bridge/articleshow/49538800.cms|title=Sudigali Sudheer spotted at tower bridge|work=tollywoodnet|access-date=26 October 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/telugu/Comedian-Sudheers-unforgettable-moment/articleshow/49674058.cms|title=Sudigali Sudheer: Comedian Sudigali Sudheer's unforggettable moment|date=5 November 2015|newspaper=The Times of India|access-date=6 May 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/telugu/blaming-the-entire-industry-for-mistakes-done-by-few-is-completely-unfair-sudigali-sudheer/articleshow/63877786.cms|title=Sudigali Sudheer: Blaming the entire industry for mistakes done by few is completely unfair|work=The Times of India|access-date=24 April 2018}}</ref> He is raised as youth icon with hosting ''[[Pove Pora]]'' , a youth game show. Before joining the Jabardasth show, he has worked as a [[Magician (illusionist)|Magician]] at [[Ramoji Film City]], [[Hyderabad]], India.\n\nMost of his skits in Jabardasth and Extra Jabardasth are hits and won the prize of the day. All his works, have good ratings on television and good views on YouTube. He has also appeared in Telugu cinemas as a supporting actor and has also hosted [[American Telugu Association|American Telugu Convention \u2013 2018]] alongside [[Suma Kanakala]]. He has secured 13th place in ''Hyderabad's Most Desirable Men on TV \u2013 for the year 2018''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/telugu/heres-to-tvs-hottest-hunks/articleshow/68024326.cms|title=Here's to TV's hottest hunks|work=The Times of India|access-date=17 February 2019}}</ref> In December 2019 he made his debut as hero in the movie Software Sudheer.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tollywood.net/software-sudheer-movie-review/|title=Software Sudheer Movie Review|work=Tollywood.Net|access-date=28 December 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.123telugu.com/reviews/software-sudheer-telugu-movie-review.html|title=Software Sudheer Telugu Movie Review|work=123Telugu.Com|access-date=28 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Early life and family ==\nSudheer Anand Bayana was born on 19<sup><sup>th</sup></sup> May 1987 in [[Vijayawada]], [[Krishna District]], Andhra Pradesh to Dev Anand Bayana and Nagarani Bayana into a Telugu speaking family. His mother Nagarani Bayana, a Housewife and father Dev Anand Bayana, worked as Manager in a Cinema theater in Vijayawada. He is one of three siblings in a family consisting of younger brother (Rohan Bayana) and elder sister (Swetha Anand Pilla). Ramya Bayana is his Sister in law(Rohan's wife).\n\nSudheer finished his schooling at ''Sri Telaprolu Bapanaiah English Medium High School'' Vijayawada.During his schooling, he was very good at dancing, singing and other extra curricular activities. He also learnt [[Bharatanatyam]], [[Folk music|Folk]], Western for two years and a good dancer during his schooldays. He participated in many competitions at various levels and had won many prizes. Magic, another area of his interest which was guided by his Maternal Uncle since childhood. Later he joined college to pursue Intermediate and opted for M.P.C.(Mathematics, Physics and Chemistry) as those were his favourite subjects. During this time he moved to Hyderabad to pursue acting career and was not able to attend final exams. After Six years,he completed the intermediate. Later he continued to work for various shows.<ref name=\":1\"/>\n\n== Acting career ==\n\n===Early Career and Struggle (2004\u20132008)===\n\nSudheer made his first Television appearance for a talent show telecasted on Citi Cable Vijayawada. During his Intermediate, he appeared for a show ''\u2018Star Hunt One Chance\u2019'' which was aired on [[Maa TV]]. His talents were highly appreciated by Judges. He skipped his intermediate exams to appear in the Finale. He was one of the finalist of ''\u2018Star Hunt One Chance\u2019''. His efforts went in vain as he did not succeed both in Exams and Show. He returned to Vijayawada where he started to teach Folk, Western and Classic form of dance.<ref name=\":1\"/>\n\nIn sudden turn of events, his father met with an accident and seriously injured. At the same time they faced financial difficulties. Being the eldest son, he took family responsibilities and moved to Hyderabad. In 2006, he joined [[Ramoji Film City]] as a Magician. Daily he used to perform three Magic shows round the year. He was greatly inspired by works of [[David Blaine]] and [[Criss Angel]].<ref name=\":1\"/> \n{{quote box\n| width = 100%\n| border = 2px\n| fontsize = 100%\n| bgcolor = #E6FBFF\n| align = center\n| quote = '' \" Film city days were the best part of my life. Those were the days of Happiness, Sadness, Hard work and Earnings. That transformed me a lot and encouraged to achieve more\"''\n| salign = right\n| source = \u2014 Sudigali Sudheer in one of his interviews in March 2017<ref name=\":1\">{{cite web|title= Sudigali Sudheer Interview |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=F-IH-kH5Cho|work=Telugu Film Nagar|accessdate=17 March 2017}}</ref>\n}}\n\n=== Comeback, Resurgence and Introduction to Small Screen (2009\u20132012)===\n\nAfter two and half years of work in Film city, he left the job to achieve acting career goals. But this decision yielded no results. With no options left, he joined and worked with ''Ali'', his Magic Guru, one of the finest Magician in Hyderabad. During those days, his earnings dried up and there were times he used to drink sink water and had no money to afford a meal. Things changed slowly, he started to conduct magic shows and game shows. He conducted magic shows for Local TV where he met Getup Srinu and Pradeep Machiraju. Later he started an event management firm and organised many shows and Events. In 2011, his Magic Talent got him an opportunity to conduct Magic show for Maa TV in a big way. Magic Mantra, Street Magic Sweet Magic, Abrakadabra shows were the first Feathers in his TV Career.<ref name=\":1\"/>\n\n=== Breakthrough and Acclaim (2013\u20132014)===\n\n'''Jabardasth'''\n\nSudheer got his career break through ''Jabardasth'', Telugu comedy television series produced by [[Mallemala]] Entertainments and telecast on [[ETV Network]]. He was one of the team members in ''\u2018Venu Wonders\u2019'' led by Venu. His first episode aired on 7 February 2013. His performance was highly appreciated by Judges Nagendra Babu and Roja. Every time he used to impress the judges and audiences with outstanding performance. He got opportunity to lead his own team, teamed up with his best friends Getup Srinu, Auto Ramprasad and Sunny to form '''''Sudigali Sudheer & Team'''''. That's when he got stage name Sudigali Sudheer. His first skit as Team leader telecasted on 15 August 2013. His team became instant hit due to his timings, expressions, Srinu's Get-ups, Ramprasad's auto punches. His team won \"Performers of the day\" many times. In an interview, he revealed that it's because of Getup Srinu he got chance to perform in ''Venu Wonders Team''.\n\n=== Rise to Stardom and Prominence (2015\u2013present)===\n\n'''Extra Jabardasth'''\n[[File:Sudigaali sudheer performing a skit from Jabardasth.png|thumbnail|right|upright=1.15|alt=|'''Sudigali Sudheer performing a skit in ''[[Extra Jabardasth]]''''' ]]\n\nSudheer's team later moved into [[Extra Jabardasth]], spin off of ''Jabardasth'' Comedy TV Series. The first episode of this show telecasted on [[ETV Network]] on 10 October 2014. The series garnered very good response from the audience. His team has won \"Performers of the day\" many times here as well. Currently all his skits are performed in Extra Jabardasth. He has also made guest appearance for other team leader's skits in ''Jabardasth'' and ''Extra Jabardasth'' on multiple occasions.\n\n'''Dhee Ultimate Dance Show (Season 9,10,11 and 12)'''\n\nSudheer got his career second best through [[Dhee Ultimate Dance Show]], south India's biggest dance reality show produced by [[Mallemala]] Entertainments and telecast on [[ETV Network]]. He made his first entry through 9<sup><sup>th</sup></sup> Season of Dhee Ultimate Dance Show as Team Leader. His comedy timings, dance, style, expressions, spontaneity received very good appreciation from the audience. He is also the Title Winner of Dhee Ultimate Dance Show Season 9 and 10 ; Runner up of Dhee Ultimate Dance Show Season 11. Currently, he is the Team Leader for the 12<sup><sup>th</sup></sup> Season of the show.\n\n'''Pove Pora'''\n\nIn 2017, Sudheer started his anchoring career with a new show ''\u2018[[Pove Pora]]\u2019'', an youth game show, co-hosted with anchor Vishnupriya, produced by [[Mallemala]] Entertainments and telecast on [[ETV Plus]]. It received good response from students who were the center theme of the show. The show completed its 100<sup><sup>th</sup></sup> episode on 15 June 2019.\n\n== Filmography ==\n\nAll the films are in Telugu language.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n\n!  Year \n!  Movie \n!  Role \n!  Note\n|-\n\n| 2013 || ''[[Adda (film)|Adda]]'' || Karthik ||\n|-\n\n| rowspan=\"4\" |2014 || ''Arya Chitra''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movie-details/arya-chitra/movieshow/62508519.cms|title=Arya Chitra Movie: Showtimes, Review, Trailer, Posters, News & Videos \u2013 eTimes|work=The Times of India}}</ref> || Hari ||\n|-\n| ''[[Race Gurram]]'' || Spandana's driver ||\n|-\n|[[Chakkiligintha]] || Pub Waiter ||\n|-\n| ''[[Brother of Bommali]]'' || Ramakrishna's friend ||\n|-\n\n| rowspan=\"5\"|2015 || ''[[Tiger (2015 film)|Tiger]]'' || Tiger's friend ||\n|-\n| [[Supreme (film)|Supreme]]||Movie Director|| \n|-\n| ''[[Where Is Vidya Balan]]'' || ||\n|-\n| ''[[Sher (film)|Sher]]'' || ||\n|-\n| ''[[Cinema Choopistha Mava]]'' || College Student ||\n|-\n\n| rowspan=\"5\"|2016|| ''[[Nenu Sailaja]]'' || Hari's friend ||\n|-\n| ''Drishya Kavyam''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.123telugu.c