 Pedagogical University\n| occupation         = {{hlist | Entrepreneur | investor }}\n| years_active       = 2000\u2013present\n| era                = \n| employer           = \n| organization       = \n| agent              = \n| known_for          = \n| notable_works      = <!-- produces label \"Notable work\"; may be overridden by |credits=, which produces label \"Notable credit(s)\"; or by |works=, which produces label \"Works\"; or by |label_name=, which produces label \"Label(s)\" -->\n| style              = \n| home_town          = \n| salary             = \n| net_worth          = [[United States dollar|US$]]3.1&nbsp;billion (April 2020)<ref name=\"Forbes\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/igor-bukhman/#2844377b2f5c/|title=#648 Dmitry Bukhman|work=Forbes|access-date=April 14, 2020}}</ref>\n| height             = <!-- \"X cm\", \"X m\" or \"X ft Y in\" plus optional reference (conversions are automatic) -->\n| television         = \n| title              = Co-founder of Playrix\n| term               = \n| predecessor        = \n| successor          = \n| party              = \n| movement           = \n| opponents          = \n| boards             = \n| criminal_charge    = <!-- Criminality parameters should be supported with citations from reliable sources -->\n| criminal_penalty   = \n| criminal_status    = \n| spouse             = <!-- Use article title or common name -->\n| partner            = <!-- (unmarried long-term partner) -->\n| children           = \n| parents            = <!-- overrides mother and father parameters -->\n| mother             = <!-- may be used (optionally with father parameter) in place of parents parameter (displays \"Parent(s)\" as label) -->\n| father             = <!-- may be used (optionally with mother parameter) in place of parents parameter (displays \"Parent(s)\" as label) -->\n| relatives          = \n| family             = \n| callsign           = \n| awards             = \n| website            = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} -->\n| module             = \n| module2            = \n| module3            = \n| module4            = \n| module5            = \n| module6            = \n| signature          = \n| signature_size     = \n| signature_alt      = \n| footnotes          = \n}}\n'''Dmitry Anatolyevich Bukhman''' ({{lang-ru|\u0414\u043c\u0438\u0442\u0440\u0438\u0439 \u0410\u043d\u0430\u0442\u043e\u043b\u044c\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0447 \u0411\u0443\u0445\u043c\u0430\u043d|translit=Dmitrij Anatol'evi\u010d Buchman}}; born May\u200c \u200c27,\u200c \u200c1985\u200c) is a Russian entrepreneur and co-founder of [[video game developer]] [[Playrix]].<ref>{{cite web|author=Novinar Novinar |url=https://russiabusinesstoday.com/featured/russian-game-developers-join-club-of-billionaires/ |title=Russian Game Developers Join Club of Billionaires |publisher=Russia Business Today |date=2019-04-18 |accessdate=2020-01-05}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Bloomberg |url=https://www.themoscowtimes.com/2019/04/18/russian-billionaire-brothers-crush-it-with-gaming-powerhouse-playrix-a65284 |title=Russian Billionaire Brothers Crush It With Gaming Powerhouse Playrix |publisher=The Moscow Times |date=2019-04-18 |accessdate=2020-01-05}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nDmitry Bukhman was born into a Jewish family in Vologda, Russia in 1985. In 2000, while studying applied math at Vologda University, Dmitry together with his brother [[Igor Bukhman|Igor]] started developing [[PC game]]s.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PvZZxXpfmtw|title=\u041a\u0430\u043a \u0431\u0440\u0430\u0442\u044c\u044f \u0411\u0443\u0445\u043c\u0430\u043d\u044b \u0441\u0442\u0430\u043b\u0438 \u043c\u0438\u043b\u043b\u0438\u0430\u0440\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043c\u0438, \u0430 \u043e\u043d\u043b\u0430\u0439\u043d \u0412\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0433\u0434\u0430 - \u0433\u043b\u043e\u0431\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e\u0439|via=www.youtube.com}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nIn 2004 Dmitry together with his brother founded [[Playrix]].<ref name=\"meduza1\">{{cite web|url=https://meduza.io/en/feature/2019/04/19/our-games-are-at-the-top-of-the-russian-charts-but-almost-nobody-knows-us-as-a-brand |title=\u2018Our games are at the top of the Russian charts, but almost nobody knows us as a brand\u2019 Two Russian brothers started a video game company and got onto Bloomberg's billionaire list. Here\u2019s their first long interview. \u2014 Meduza |publisher=Meduza.io |date=2019-04-19 |accessdate=2020-01-05}}</ref> Playrix had been working in the market of casual PC games until 2009 and had produced about 30 games by then. In 2009 the studio focused on developing free-to-play games for smartphones and tablets.\nIn 2011 the company moved the headquarters from Vologda to [[Dublin]], [[Ireland]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://hbr-russia.ru/management/operatsionnoe-upravlenie/809875 |title=Harvard Business Review|publisher=Hbr-russia.ru |date=2019-09-09 |accessdate=2020-01-05}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.ru/newsroom/tehnologii/388831-razrabotchiki-igr-iz-vologdy-predskazali-popadanie-v-odnu-ligu-s |title=\u0420\u0430\u0437\u0440\u0430\u0431\u043e\u0442\u0447\u0438\u043a\u0438 \u0438\u0433\u0440 \u0438\u0437 \u0412\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0433\u0434\u044b \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0441\u043a\u0430\u0437\u0430\u043b\u0438 \u043f\u043e\u043f\u0430\u0434\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u0432 \u043e\u0434\u043d\u0443 \u043b\u0438\u0433\u0443 \u0441 \u0441\u043e\u0437\u0434\u0430\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044f\u043c\u0438 Call of Duty \u0438 Warcraft \u043f\u043e \u0434\u043e\u0445\u043e\u0434\u0430\u043c &#124; \u0422\u0435\u0445\u043d\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0433\u0438\u0438 |publisher=Forbes.ru |date=2019-12-05 |accessdate=2020-01-05}}</ref> In 2013 the first mobile game [[Township (video game)|Township]] was released.<ref name=\"Bloomberg\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2019-04-17/billionaire-brothers-crushing-it-with-gaming-powerhouse-playrix |title=Playrix Founders Are Billionaires on Games Fishdom, Gardenscapes |publisher=Bloomberg |date=2019-04-17 |accessdate=2020-01-05}}</ref> As of December 2019 the company operates 5 free-to-play mobile games (Township, [[Fishdom]], [[Gardenscapes]], [[Homescapes]], and [[Wildscapes]]).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://vc.ru/flood/33117-esli-tempy-rosta-sohranyatsya-postroenie-kompanii-urovnya-activision-blizzard-ili-ea-zaymet-ne-tak-mnogo-vremeni |title=Activision Blizzard |publisher=Vc.ru |date=2018-02-10 |accessdate=2020-01-05}}</ref> According to AppAnnie analytics, it is one of the Top 5 grossing mobile publishers worldwide.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.appannie.com/en/insights/app-annie-news/top-52-app-publishers-2018/ |title=App Annie\u2019s Top 52 Publishers of 2018 &#124; App Annie Blog |publisher=Appannie.com |date= |accessdate=2020-01-05}}</ref> The company has 2,000 employees and 25 offices.<ref name=\"meduza1\"/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.ru/milliardery/395447-kak-bratya-buhmany-postroili-odnu-iz-krupneyshih-igrovyh-kompaniy-v-mire-playrix|title=\u041a\u0430\u043a \u0431\u0440\u0430\u0442\u044c\u044f \u0411\u0443\u0445\u043c\u0430\u043d\u044b \u043f\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0440\u043e\u0438\u043b\u0438 \u043e\u0434\u043d\u0443 \u0438\u0437 \u043a\u0440\u0443\u043f\u043d\u0435\u0439\u0448\u0438\u0445 \u0438\u0433\u0440\u043e\u0432\u044b\u0445 \u043a\u043e\u043c\u043f\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0439 \u0432 \u043c\u0438\u0440\u0435 \u2014 Playrix \u2014 \u0438 \u0441\u0442\u0430\u043b\u0438 \u043c\u0438\u043b\u043b\u0438\u0430\u0440\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043c\u0438|website=www.forbes.ru|language=ru|access-date=2020-04-15}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, Dmitry together with his brother Igor acquired a stake in video games developer Nexters Global.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/dmitry-bukhman-1/|title=Dmitry Bukhman|website=Forbes|language=en|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n\nAs of 2019 eight mobile game developers have already been acquired by Playrix.<ref name=\"pocketgamer1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.pocketgamer.biz/interview/72200/playrixs-stellar-2019/|title=1,700 staff, 20 games in development, 8 acquisitions, 2 billion dollar games: Playrix's stellar 2019|last1=Forde|first1=Matthew|last2=Writer|first2=Staff|website=pocketgamer.biz}}</ref> Among the biggest acquires and investments are: Serbian Eipix,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pocketgamer.biz/news/72127/playrix-buys-eipix-entertainment/|title=Playrix acquires Serbian game studio Eipix Entertainment|first1=Matthew|last1=Forde|first2=Staff|last2=Writer|website=pocketgamer.biz}}</ref> Ukrainian Zagrava <ref>{{cite web|url=https://ain.ua/en/2019/10/29/playrix-acquires-zagrava-games/ |title=Russian Playrix acquires Ukrainian Zagrava Games for an estimated $1M |publisher=AIN.UA |date= |accessdate=2020-01-05}}</ref> and Belarussian Vizor game studios.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2019-12-05/playrix-billionaires-battle-activision-by-snapping-up-studios?srnd=technology-vp |title=Playrix Mobile Gaming Billionaires Take On Activision, EA Sports |publisher=Bloomberg |date=2019-12-05 |accessdate=2020-01-05}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.facebook.com/dmitri.bukhman Bukhman Facebook account]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bukhman, Dmitry}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Vologda]]\n[[Category:Russian billionaires]]\n[[Category:21st-century Russian businesspeople]]\n[[Category:1985 births]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Russian entrepreneur}}\n{{Infobox person\n| honorific_prefix   = \n| name               = Dmitry Anatolyevich Bukhman\n| honorific_suffix   = \n| image              = File:\u0414\u0438\u043c\u0430 3.jpg\n| image_upright      = \n| landscape          = <!-- yes, if wide image, otherwise leave blank -->\n| alt                = <!-- descriptive text for use by speech synthesis (text-to-speech) software -->\n| caption            = Dmitry Bukhman in 2018\n| native_name        = \u0414\u043c\u0438\u0442\u0440\u0438\u0439 \u0410